15/12/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Minister of Transport and Communications Mile Janakieski and Bulgarian Minister of Transport Petar Mutafchiev vowed on Thursday (December 14th) in Skopje to step up co-operation, particularly in terms of the Pan-European Transport Corridor 8 projects.
They also agreed on the opening of three new border crossings next year, as well as completion of the railway infrastructure from Kumanovo to the Bulgarian border.
They also looked at air traffic, and the possibility of opening new routes, such as Ohrid-Skopje-Sofia or Ohrid-Varna.
(MIA, Makfax - 14/12/06)
